ary, yet hopeful account of learning by example that acknowledges the power of social contexts in shaping human lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEducationxPhilosophy. 0aExample. 0aImitation. 0aLearning, Psychology of. 4aPsychology : Cognitive Science. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147848640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791478486423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791478486/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles